snippet.title: Homemade Worcestershire Sauce | Easy & Delicious
snippet.description:
I am making homemade Worcestershire sauce. Worcestershire sauce is something I use all the time & always keep in the pantry, so when I discovered you can make your own I was so happy. And its way better when you make it yourself. I hope you give this recipe a try!

Worcestershire sauce:
1/2 cup Balsamic Vinegar
1/4 cup Molasses 
1/4 cup Apple Cider Vinegar (or white vinegar)
1/4 cup Coconut Aminos (or soy sauce)
1 tsp Fish Sauce
Juice of 1 Lemon or Lime
1 tsp Black pepper
2 tsp Garlic powder
2 tsp Onion powder
1/2 tsp Turmeric 
Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator months!

Original recipe came from Carol over at Thrifty Chic House wife. I hope you go check her video out! https://youtu.be/KEmNiPIfSuM

8C ketchup
2 1/2 brown sugar
3T onion powder
3T garlic powder
3T dried mustard
2t smoked paprika
1t Cayenne 
1t chili powder
1T black pepper
3T salt

snippet.description:

Recipe Amounts:
Powdered Sugar - For every 1 Cup of cane sugar do 1 TBS Arrowroot Powder or Corn Starch
Brown Sugar - For every 1 cup cane sugar do 1 TBS Molasses (I did 2 TBS for a really dark brown sugar) Do less molasses if you want a light brown sugar.
